# Website Revamp Template

This is a **reusable Laravel revamp starter**, NOT a finished client site. When the user sends a website URL and asks to revamp it, customize the entire project to match that website.

## Before Any Revamp

1. Read `REVAMP.md` in project root for full workflow
2. Read `config/site.php` — this is the single source of truth for brand, theme, pages, and features
3. Visit/analyze the target URL the user provides

## What to Customize Per Revamp

| Area | Files |
|------|-------|
| Brand & config | `config/site.php`, `.env` (SITE_* vars) |
| Navigation | `config/site.php` → `pages`, `routes/web.php` |
| Public pages | `resources/views/website/*.blade.php` |
| Layouts | `resources/views/layouts/website/` (already config-driven) |
| Theme/CSS | `public/assets/website/css/site.css` + theme colors in config |
| JS | `public/assets/website/js/site.js` |
| Admin branding | Auto from `$site` config; adjust `features` flags for modules |
| Admin sidebar | `resources/views/layouts/admin/sidebar.blade.php` |

## Key Conventions

- All layouts use `$site` config (shared via AppServiceProvider) — never hardcode brand names
- Use `site('key')` helper in PHP, `$site['key']` in Blade
- Public pages extend `layouts.website.master`
- Admin pages extend `layouts.admin.app`
- Add new pages: config → route → WebController method → blade view
- Remove placeholder content and replace with real client content
- Enable only the admin modules the client needs via `config/site.php` → `features`

## Do NOT

- Hardcode client-specific brand names in layouts (use config)
- Leave Lectrolab/Lyllianna/Phoenix legacy references
- Skip admin dashboard branding update
- Forget to update `.env` SITE_* variables alongside config

## Empty Template Defaults

- Site name: "Your Website"
- Pages: Home, About, Contact
- Theme: dark mode, blue/cyan accent
- Admin: matches site config automatically
